docs.abstract: The tobacco and vaping industries and conservative allies intensively lobbied against a ban on popular flavored e-cigarettes.
docs.snippet: The tobacco and vaping industries and conservative allies intensively lobbied against a ban on popular flavored e-cigarettes.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Trump administration is expected to announce this week that it will ban mint-, fruit- and dessert-flavored e-cigarette cartridges popular with teenagers, but allow menthol and tobacco flavors to remain on the market.

headline.main: F.D.A. Plans to Ban Most E-Cigarette Flavors but Menthol
headline.print_headline: U.S. Set to Ban Vaping Flavors Teens Use Most

docs.abstract: Giving the vaccine intravenously to monkeys provided 90% protection against tuberculosis. More testing is needed before humans can be inoculated that way.

docs.lead_paragraph: In the constant search for a vaccine against tuberculosis — which now kills more people around the world than any other infectious disease — researchers have made an unusual discovery.

docs.abstract: Bush fire season is nothing new to Australians, but this summer has been calamitous — and it’s far from over.
docs.snippet: Bush fire season is nothing new to Australians, but this summer has been calamitous — and it’s far from over.
docs.lead_paragraph: This fire season has been one of the worst in Australia’s history, with at least 15 people killed, hundreds of homes destroyed and millions of acres burned. And summer is far from over.

headline.main: Why the Fires in Australia Are So Bad
headline.print_headline: Why the Fire Season In Australia Is So Bad

docs.abstract: His marketing vision turned the world’s premier professional basketball league into a global brand with its biggest stars as its ambassadors.
docs.snippet: His marketing vision turned the world’s premier professional basketball league into a global brand with its biggest stars as its ambassadors.
docs.lead_paragraph: David Stern, who during a 30-year run as commissioner of the National Basketball Association masterminded its transformation from a league in peril to a multibillion-dollar industry and the first American sports league to thrive internationally, died on Wednesday in Manhattan. He was 77.

headline.main: David Stern, Transformative N.B.A. Commissioner, Dies at 77
headline.print_headline: David Stern, 77, Architect of the Modern N.B.A., Is Dead

docs.abstract: More cyclists were killed last year than in any year in two decades. Safety groups are calling on Mayor Bill de Blasio to  strengthen his efforts.
docs.snippet: More cyclists were killed last year than in any year in two decades. Safety groups are calling on Mayor Bill de Blasio to  strengthen his efforts.
docs.lead_paragraph: As New York City tackled the stubborn problem of street safety in recent years, it earned praise for pushing down traffic deaths to their lowest level in a century and helped begin a national movement to make roads safer for pedestrians and cyclists.

headline.main: More People Are Dying on New York City’s Streets. What Went Wrong?
headline.print_headline: What Went Wrong With the Vision Zero Traffic Safety Initiative?

docs.abstract: Embracing honesty changed my life. Maybe it can change yours.
docs.snippet: Embracing honesty changed my life. Maybe it can change yours.
docs.lead_paragraph: Two years ago, I started being honest. Actually, that’s a lie. I merely started noticing when I wasn’t being honest — and more important, why. I wrote about it in an essay called “How Honesty Could Make You Happier,” which documented what I learned from keeping an honesty journal.

headline.main: New Year’s Resolution: Be More Honest
